This project uses the **GMP (GNU MP Library)**, which is licensed under the **LGPL v3.0**.

You can redistribute and/or modify the GMP library under the terms of the LGPL as published by the Free Software Foundation. See the full text of the LGPL for details. Here are the key obligations of the LGPL:

1. **Library Replacement**: If you distribute this program with GMP, you must ensure that users have the ability to replace the version of GMP used, if desired. This can be done by including object files or providing a method to recompile the program with a different version of the GMP library.

2. **Source Code**: If you have modified the GMP library, you must make the modified source code available. If you have not modified the GMP library, you must provide clear instructions on how users can obtain the source code of the GMP library.

3. **Distribution**: When redistributing the program, either modified or unmodified, you must include a copy of the LGPL v3.0 with the software and provide information on how users can obtain the GMP source code.

You can find the full text of the LGPL here: [https://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl-3.0.html](https://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl-3.0.html).

The source code for GMP is available at: [https://gmplib.org/](https://gmplib.org/).
